Natural Language Licenses to RDF
--------------------------------
Text clasification tool for transforming natural language licenses to ODRL RDF data.

Requirements:
------------
- Java JRE 1.7
- Perl 5.16.2 or above

Usage:
-----
To start the learning process give execution permissions to the "learner" file or use: `perl learner`:

./learner -t <TAGGED_DIR> -u <UNTAGGED_DIR> -o <OUTPUT_DIR> [-q <NUMBER_OF_QUERIES>] [-f <FILTER_TAGGED_CORPUS>] [-g <FILTER_UNTAGGED_CORPUS>] [--passive]

Options:
-------
  TAGGED_DIR             Directory with the annotated files in conll format
  UNTAGGED_DIR           Directory with the unannotated files in conll format
  OUTPUT_DIR             Directory where results are written
  NUMBER_OF_QUERIES      Amount of queries in each step of the Active Learning algorithm (defaults to 5)
  FILTER_TAGGED_CORPUS   Filter of features for annotated corpus (default to 0)
  FILTER_UNTAGGED_CORPUS Filter of features for unannotated corpus (default to 10)
  passive                If flagged, the sampling of the unannotated corpus is random (doesn't use active learning approach)